      {
        "id": "afbe825186b517962c37223b6321407b75fb4a20",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-17 20:42:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFor ONAP demo those topics are fixed.   For DCAE, they don't use the \"standard\" name DCAE-CL-EVENT but instead \"unauthenticated.TCA_EVENT_OUTPUT\".   \n\nIn any ways, moving forward (I still have to do the changes), I'm planning to add \n\"topic nicknames\" so drl templates remain immutable to topic naming changes.   The simple idea is that a topic can be its nickname and viceversa.  The main point of it is that the template does not change, case another component decides not to use the standard name (ie. DCAE-DL-EVENT, APPC-CL, and POLICY-CL-MGT)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
